(2) A refugee officer may give such orders or directions, either orally or in writing, to any refugee as may be necessary or expedient for the following purposes, that is to say: (a) to ensure that any refugee settlement is administered in an orderly and efficient manner; (b) to ensure the performance of any work or duty necessary for the maintenance of essential services in any refugee settlement or for the general welfare of the refugees therein; (c) to ensure that all proper precautions are taken to preserve the health and well-being of the refugees therein; (d) to preserve orderly conduct and discipline in any refugee settlement .
