(3) Any refugee who— (a) without a permit in that behalf issued under section twelve, leaves or attempts to leave a refugee settlement in which he has been ordered to reside; or (b) in a refugee settlement disobeys any rules made by the Minister, any direction of the Commissioner or any order or direction of a refugee officer , made or given under this section; or (c) in a refugee settlement conducts himself in a manner prejudicial to good order and discipline; shall be guilty of an offence against this Act.
